<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890600>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. Hippasteria phrygiana (North Atlantic, South Pacific). USNM 14361 North Atlantic. Scale bar = 1.0 cm. A, abactinal surface. B, actinal surface. C, marginal plate series. USNM E13768 New Zealand. D, abactinal surface. E, marginal plate series. F, actinal surface showing furrow and mouth spines. G and H show USNM E46619 and MNHN (Paris) EcAs 10683, respectively, at R = ∼4.5–5.0. I, CASIZ 113374 British Columbia. J, CASIZ 173038 Aleutians. Lateral view showing abactinal spines, pedicellariae, and marginal plates." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4890600/files/figure.png" .

